Hey All,

I wanted to share with you about the Venkat Panchapakesan Memorial
Scholarship
.
It
is for students in India who are passionate, ever optimistic, and want to
use computer science to make the world a more sustainable place.

We are specifically looking for university students who:

   

   Aspire to be computer scientists and technology leaders
   

   Exemplify leadership skills and a demonstrated passion for computer
   science and technology
   

   Assist those around them to excel in the field of computer science and
   technology
   

   Help their friends and family members use computer science and technology
   

   Leverage the field of computer science to transform systems (from
   building the next game changing technology, to even helping families be
   happy, etc.)
    Have faced adversity and overcome it to continue learning and growing
   in the field of computer science


To be eligible to apply, applicants must:

   

   Be currently enrolled as an undergraduate or graduate student in a
   college/university in India, for the 201516 and 201617 academic year
   

   Be currently pursuing a degree in computer science, computer engineering
   or a closely related technical field


Please see the scholarship link

for more details.

It's a fantastic opportunity, and I request you to share on your
campuses and in your networks. If there are any students that you know
personally, who fit the description above, do encourage them to apply!

Please let me know if you have any questions.

Cheers



 


